
========================================================================
=== C1 empirical: drive fixed, measure equilibrium rate ===
========================================================================

Prediction under layers.py form (rate_next = leak*state + phi):
  equilibrium rate = phi(drive) / (1 - leak) = phi(drive) * τ/dt

Prediction under standard Euler (lgn_l4 form):
  equilibrium rate = phi(drive)

Config: L23E τ=20ms, dt=5ms, leak=0.750, drive=0.5
  phi(drive)           = 0.280930
  predicted r_eq       = phi/(1-leak) = 1.123719
  standard Euler r_eq  = phi          = 0.280930
  τ/dt gain            = 4.000

  Running: r_{t+1} = leak*r_t + phi(drive):
   step           r
      0    0.000000
      1    0.280930
     10    1.060439
     50    1.123719
    100    1.123719
    200    1.123719
    500    1.123719
  final r = 1.123719
  |observed - predicted| / predicted = 2.1217e-07  =>  CONFIRMED

